<body lang=EN-US style='word-wrap:break-word'>

<div class=WordSection1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;line-height:normal'><b><span
style='font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Cholestasis
of pregnancy</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>What is cholestasis of
pregnancy</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Cholestasis of pregnancy is a
reversible pathological condition of the liver, which is characterized by a
violation of the outflow of bile from the liver into the duodenum.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In English, this pathology is
called intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Causes</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The cause of cholestasis
during pregnancy is not fully understood.&nbsp;Most likely, genetic factors and
hormonal changes during pregnancy - an increase in estrogen levels - are of
primary importance, which explains the frequency of occurrence of the disease
in the third trimester of pregnancy, when the level of these hormones reaches a
maximum.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The development of cholestasis
is based on a violation of the outflow of bile from the liver, which leads to
the accumulation of the bile pigment bilirubin in the blood and a decrease in
the flow of bile into the intestine, which disrupts the normal digestion of
food.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Who is at risk</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Women whose previous pregnancy also proceeded with the development
of cholestasis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Women with liver disease.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Women with multiple pregnancies.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Women over 35.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>How often does it occur</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The prevalence of cholestasis
in pregnant women varies from 0.5 to 27%, depending on racial and ethnic origin
and geographical location.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Symptoms</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Severe itching is the main
symptom of cholestasis of pregnancy.&nbsp;Most women feel itching on their
palms or soles of their feet, but some feel it everywhere.&nbsp;It often gets
worse at night and can be so strong that sleep is disturbed.&nbsp;Itching most
often occurs in the third trimester of pregnancy, but can sometimes start
earlier.&nbsp;As the term of childbirth approaches, it may increase, but after
childbirth it gradually disappears.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Other, less common symptoms:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>jaundice;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>nausea;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>loss of appetite.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Diagnosis of the
disease</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Interrogation and
inspection</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The survey includes the
collection of anamnesis: the presence of chronic liver disease, how the
previous pregnancy proceeded, the severity of itching, sleep disturbances.&nbsp;On
examination, the doctor assesses the condition of the skin, the severity of
yellowness of the skin and sclera, palpates the abdomen, assesses the presence
or absence of peripheral edema, and measures blood pressure.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Laboratory examination</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Complete blood count&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>to assess the level of red
blood cells, hemoglobin.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Biochemical blood test:&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>ALT, AST, total
bilirubin, direct and indirect bilirubin, GGTP.&nbsp;Cholestasis of pregnancy
is characterized by an increase in the level of total and direct bilirubin, ALT
and AST, GGTP increases slightly.&nbsp;When cholestasis syndrome is detected,
weekly monitoring of biochemical parameters is indicated.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Coagulogram&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>- determination of prothrombin
time, INR, tk.&nbsp;these indicators depend on the normal function of the
liver.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Virological screening&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>- hepatitis A, B (HBsAg), C
(HCV), cytomegalovirus, Epstein-Barr virus.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Autoimmune antibodies&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>(antinuclear (ANA) to liver
and kidney microsomal antigen type 1 (anti-LKM1), perinuclear antineutrophil
cytoplasmic antibodies (p-ANCA) to rule out autoimmune hepatitis.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Functional, radiation
and instrumental diagnostics</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ultrasound examination of the abdominal organs&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>.&nbsp;This
study is carried out to exclude cholelithiasis, which can also cause
cholestasis.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>MRI of the abdominal organs&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is
indicated in case of difficult diagnosis of cholestasis syndrome.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Doppler ultrasound of placental blood flow&nbsp;</span></b><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is
mandatory&nbsp;from the 24th week of pregnancy and&nbsp;<b>cardiotocography&nbsp;</b>from
the 30th week 1-2 times a week.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Treatment Goals</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Relief of symptoms.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Prevention of complications for mother and fetus.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Lifestyle and aids</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>It is recommended to adhere to
a balanced healthy diet throughout pregnancy, with the development of
cholestasis, these recommendations remain.&nbsp;You should reduce the
consumption of foods high in sugar, processed meat, fatty foods.&nbsp;At least
8-10 glasses of water should be consumed per day.&nbsp;Baths with cool water,
moisturizing lotions for the skin can help to relieve itching.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Medications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ursodeoxycholic acid - the drug can reduce the concentration of
toxic bile acids, has a hepatoprotective effect.&nbsp;Treatment is continued
until delivery or until the relief of cholestasis in the postpartum period.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Ademetionine is a drug for the treatment of metabolic disorders.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Procedures</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Plasmapheresis&nbsp;</span></b><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>is a procedure for taking
blood from the body, purifying it and returning it back.&nbsp;It is prescribed
for severe symptoms, the absence of the effect of drug therapy and the
development of blood clotting disorders.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Symbol;color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>With a deterioration in the condition of a woman or fetus, with a
deterioration in laboratory parameters,&nbsp;<b>delivery is indicated for a
period of 36-37 weeks&nbsp;</b>.&nbsp;</span><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Natural delivery is
preferable to caesarean section.&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Surgery</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>In some cases, operative
delivery by caesarean section is indicated.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=RU style='font-size:
18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Possible Complications</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-18.0pt;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Reduced vitamin K levels due to malabsorption of fats, which will
lead to increased bleeding.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span lang=RU style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=RU style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>premature birth.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Respiratory disorders in a child as a result of swallowing
meconium, which enters the amniotic fluid in pregnant women with cholestasis.</span></p>

